3️⃣ Production — Logs & Testing
🔹 Logging
Structured Logging
Include timestamp, user_id, transaction_id, model_version, input features, output predictions
Levels
DEBUG → detailed info during development
INFO → normal operation logs
WARNING/ERROR → abnormal events or failures
Monitoring
Logs feed alerting systems for anomalies or failures
🔹 Testing
Unit Testing
Test each function: preprocessing, feature extraction, model prediction
Integration Testing
Ensure ML model, API, Kafka, database work end-to-end
Scenario Testing
Simulate missing data, out-of-range values, or slow data streams
Regression Testing
After model version updates, ensure no performance degradation
🔹 Python Example — Logging & Testing
import logging

# Logging setup
logging.basicConfig(filename="ml_prod.log", level=logging.INFO,
                    format='%(asctime)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s')

# Example logging
user_id, prediction = 1, "BUY"
logging.info(f"User {user_id} prediction: {prediction}")

# Simple unit test
def test_prediction():
    assert prediction in ["BUY", "SELL", "HOLD"], "Invalid prediction"

test_prediction()

GS-Level Reasoning:

Structured logs → audit, compliance, and debugging
Testing ensures robustness before live deployment
Unit + integration + regression → enterprise-grade pipeline readiness
4️⃣ Scenario-Based Questions — GS-Level
Scenario	How to Answer
“Model underperforms in production”	Check data drift, retrain using latest data, ensure preprocessing matches training pipeline, validate metrics, monitor logs.
“Missing input features in production”	Implement default values or fallback, log warnings, alert the operations team.
“Integration pipeline fails”	Test each microservice, check Kafka/queue offsets, ensure API response contracts match expectations.
“Logs too large or slow system”	Implement structured logging with retention, batch logs, or use centralized logging systems like ELK/Prometheus/Grafana.
“New ML version deployment”	Use blue-green or canary deployment, run regression tests, monitor performance metrics closely.
